    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Frustrated Customers</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sydney J Steinhardt letter on July 20 article on the poor quality of customer service in high-tech retailing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>I purchased an eMachines 466id tower, which, after five months, began to mysteriously and randomly turn itself on. The company told me that the unit was ''ghost booting'' -- the consequence of a bad motherboard. I sent my computer back and  will be given a refurbished machine.  When I complained, the customer service representative laughed. So I wrote to the company's public relations person, who has not responded.</p>
        <p>SYDNEY J. STEINHARDT  New York</p>
      </block>
